sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT member_id) AS opened_users_count
FROM marketing_messages
WHERE opened_at IS NOT NULL;

external_knowledge:
- "Active users" refers to users with a status of 'active' in the database; 
- "Engaged with marketing messages" means users who have both opened and clicked on the messages;
- "Multiple tags" refers to users who have more than one distinct tag associated with them.

sql:
SELECT member_id, COUNT(message_id) AS total_messages_sent
FROM marketing_messages
GROUP BY member_id;
